+# PS-03D5-3 Implementation Report — Create Account Backend, Runtime Disabled
+
+## Summary
+
+Implemented the Create Account backend contract and HTTP handler while keeping it **runtime disabled**. The public `POST /api/games/{gameId}/accounts` route still returns HTTP 403. The handler is exported, fully mapped to the OpenAPI contract, and covered by integration tests mounted in a dedicated test-only Express app.
+
+## Files Changed
+
+### Contract & generated clients
+- `lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml`
+  - Added `POST /api/games/{gameId}/accounts` (`operationId: createAccount`) with request/response contracts.
+  - Added `DuplicateFieldName` enum (`psnEmail`, `familyManagementEmail`, `onlineId`).
+  - Tightened `DuplicateWarningResponse` to require `code: DUPLICATE_WARNING` and the enum.
+  - Removed `format: date` from `birthDate` so Orval generates a valid Zod string+regex schema.
+- `lib/api-client-react/src/generated/api.ts`
+- `lib/api-client-react/src/generated/api.schemas.ts`
+- `lib/api-zod/src/generated/api.ts`
+- `lib/api-zod/src/generated/types/*`
+  - Regenerated by Orval; no manual edits.
+
+### Backend implementation
+- `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/accounts.ts`
+  - Added exported `createAccountHandler`.
+  - Handler maps domain errors to HTTP codes (404, 409, 500) and returns safe `AccountDetailResponse`.
+  - Production router's `POST` route remains a hard 403.
+- `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/accounts.create.test.ts` (new)
+  - 17 integration tests covering the handler and public 403 behavior.
+- `artifacts/api-server/test-loader.mjs` (new)
+  - Local ESM loader so `node --test` can import source handlers without modifying generated clients.
+- `artifacts/api-server/package.json`
+  - Test script now uses `node --import ./test-loader.mjs --test ...`.
+- `artifacts/api-server/src/*.ts`
+  - Added `.ts` extensions to relative imports so the source test loader can resolve them. No behavior change.
+
+### Tests updated
+- `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/account-contract.test.ts`
+  - Now expects `createAccount` operation and generated `useCreateAccount` hook, while still forbidding update/delete/secret/backup-code hooks.
+
+### Documentation
+- `docs/CURRENT_PHASE.md` — status updated to COMPLETED, closure notes added.
+- `docs/DECISION_LOG.md` — PS-03D5-3 closure entry added.
+
+## Runtime Changes
+
+- `POST /api/games/{gameId}/accounts` remains disabled at runtime: returns HTTP 403 with `Account operations are not authorized`.
+- The `createAccountHandler` is exported but **not** mounted in the production router.
+- When the handler is mounted in tests, it:
+  - Accepts `CreateAccountRequest` and a path `gameId`.
+  - Returns HTTP 201 with `AccountDetailResponse` (safe DTO, no secrets/passwords/backup codes/customer info).
+  - Returns HTTP 409 `DUPLICATE_WARNING` for unconfirmed duplicates, with only field names.
+  - Maps `GameNotFoundError` → 404, `InactiveGameError` → 409, `IdentifierConflictError` → 409, `EncryptionError` → 500.
+- No schema or migration changes; no runtime Account mutation activation.
+
+## Documentation-Only Changes
+
+- `docs/CURRENT_PHASE.md`
+- `docs/DECISION_LOG.md`
+
+## Tests and Results
+
+| Suite | Command | Result |
+|-------|---------|--------|
+| Workspace typecheck | `pnpm run typecheck` | Pass |
+| API server build | `pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run build` | Pass |
+| API server tests | `pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run test` | 94 tests, 7 suites, all pass |
+| Playsyncer build | `PORT=8080 BASE_PATH=/playsyncer pnpm --filter @workspace/playsyncer run build` | Pass |
+| Playsyncer tests | `pnpm --filter @workspace/playsyncer run test` | 47 tests pass |
+| Mockup sandbox build | `PORT=8081 BASE_PATH=/mockup-sandbox pnpm --filter @workspace/mockup-sandbox run build` | Pass |
+| Frontend boundary check | `grep useCreateAccount/createAccount` in `artifacts/playsyncer/src` | No imports found |
+
+### API server test highlights
+- Public route 403 with no writes.
+- 201 creation returns safe `AccountDetailResponse`.
+- Capacity template and Backup Codes are created.
+- 404 for missing/deleted game.
+- 409 for inactive game.
+- 400 for invalid UUID, email, birthDate, empty backup codes, whitespace backup codes, unexpected fields, `statusOverride`.
+- Path `gameId` wins over body `gameId`.
+- Unconfirmed duplicate → 409 `DUPLICATE_WARNING` with `DuplicateFieldName` enum values, no writes.
+- Confirmed duplicate → 201.
+- Missing encryption key → 500 with no writes.
+
+## Database Impact
+
+- No schema changes.
+- No migrations added.
+- No shared/live database modifications.
+- Existing tables used: `games`, `accounts`, `account_capacities`, `account_backup_codes`.
+
+## Known Risks
+
+- The test loader (`test-loader.mjs`) is a local workaround for Node ESM resolution of extensionless imports in source files. It is only used in the API server test script. If the project moves to explicit `.ts` imports everywhere, the loader can be removed.
+- The frontend `playsyncer` runtime currently shows a pre-existing `useGames must be used inside <GamesProvider>` error (from PS-03D5-2). This is unrelated to the Create Account backend changes and is not addressed in this sub-stage.
+- Root `pnpm run build` requires `PORT`/`BASE_PATH` for Vite-based artifacts; the per-artifact builds were run with explicit values.
+
+## Rollback Steps
+
+1. Revert `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/accounts.ts` to remove the exported handler and `.ts` import extensions (or revert only the handler block).
+2. Revert `artifacts/api-server/package.json` test script.
+3. Remove `artifacts/api-server/test-loader.mjs` and `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/accounts.create.test.ts`.
+4. Revert OpenAPI changes: `git checkout lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml` and regenerate clients.
+5. Revert documentation changes: `docs/CURRENT_PHASE.md`, `docs/DECISION_LOG.md`.
+6. No database rollback needed because no schema or migration changes were applied.
